        "title": "Fix delivery-ready verification blockers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR closes the remaining delivery-ready verification blockers for the current branch.\n\nIt completes three founder-visible fixes:\n- suppress non-actionable historical task delivery warning noise on operator surfaces\n- normalize heartbeat `0m` semantics across status and health surfaces\n- improve async exec approval followup messaging so user-visible replies stop leaking raw internal execution metadata\n\nIt also fixes the final type-surface issues discovered during fresh closure verification.\n\n## What changed\n\n### Task registry / operator surface\n- stop surfacing already-non-actionable historical succeeded tasks as actionable delivery failure noise\n- preserve stored task history while cleaning the reconciled read/audit surface\n\n### Heartbeat status consistency\n- align `0m` heartbeat semantics across `status --deep` and `health --json`\n- remove contradictory reporting between status surfaces\n\n### Async exec followup messaging\n- prefer internal continuation plus synthesized user-facing results\n- avoid leaking raw gateway/session/exit metadata into normal chat replies\n\n### Closure verification fixes\n- fix the type/test-surface issues found during fresh `pnpm check`\n- keep the final closure edits minimal and scoped to the failing surfaces\n\n## Verification\n\nFresh verification on this branch:\n- `pnpm lint` ✅\n- `pnpm check` ✅\n- `pnpm build` ✅\n\nPreviously targeted verification for the repaired slices also passed:\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/tasks/task-registry.test.ts` ✅\n- `pnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.agents.config.ts src/agents/bash-tools.exec-approval-followup.test.ts` ✅\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/commands/health.command.coverage.test.ts src/commands/status-all/diagnosis.test.ts` ✅\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/config/doc-baseline.integration.test.ts test/release-check.test.ts test/openclaw-npm-postpublish-verify.test.ts` ✅\n\n## Notes\n\nAn earlier assumption that repo-wide extension lint debt was the remaining blocker did not hold under fresh verification. The real final blockers were a small set of type-surface failures, which are fixed here.\n",
